devdoc.details: Wallet contract enables dex users  to store their cryptocurrencies

addToken(bytes32,address).details: Allows users to add the capability of  storing a paticular Token on the wallet

params.ticker: Represents the symbol(ticker) of the Token
params.tokenAddress: Represents the address for the Token being added

deposit(uint256,bytes32).details: Allows users to deposit tokens onto their wallet

params.amount: Represents the amount of tokens being deposited
params.ticker: Represents the symbol(ticker) of the token being deposited

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw(uint256,bytes32).details: Allows users to withraw tokens from wallet

params.amount: Represents the amount of tokens being withdrawn
params.ticker: Represents the symbol(ticker) of the tokens being withdrawn
